## 3. THE DECISION DOOR FILTER (EXECUTION SPEED RUNTIME)
To out-execute traditional organizations, bypass analytical paralysis by categorizing every choice through a binary gate.

*   **🚪 ONE-WAY DOORS (High Risk / Irreversible):** Decisions with massive financial or structural lock-in (e.g., quitting a job, signing long-term leases, shifting core data architecture). 
    *   *Protocol:* Slow down. Run deep system dependency mapping and risk mitigation loops.
*   **🚪 TWO-WAY DOORS (Low Risk / Reversible):** Decisions that can be changed or undone in 15 minutes with near-zero cost (e.g., pricing tweaks, landing page copy, visual mockup layouts).
    *   *Protocol:* **Immediate execution.** Maximize velocity. If it fails, iterate the variables in real-time.